# DealerScope — Cursor AI Rules
# Injected into every Cursor session automatically

## Platform
Wholesale vehicle arbitrage platform. Scrapes government auctions, scores deals using institutional dealer logic, surfaces profitable vehicles to buy below MMR and resell to dealers at Manheim.

## Non-Negotiable Business Rules (ENFORCE ALWAYS)
- Bid ceiling: Premium = 88% of MMR all-in | Standard = 80% of MMR all-in
- Min gross margin: Premium = $1,500 | Standard = $2,500
- Min ROI: hot >20%, good >12%
- Max vehicle age: 4 years (NO EXCEPTIONS in scoring)
- Max mileage: 50,000 miles (NO EXCEPTIONS in scoring)
- High-rust states HARD REJECT: OH, MI, PA, NY, WI, MN, IL, IN, MO, IA, ND, SD, NE, KS, WV, ME, NH, VT, MA, RI, CT, NJ, MD, DE
- Exception: Vehicles <= currentYear - 2 bypass rust state rejection (newer cars haven't rusted yet)
- DOS score threshold: >= 50 to save, >= 65 for Rover display, >= 80 for alert

## DOS Scoring Formula
Margin×0.35 + Velocity×0.25 + Segment×0.20 + Model×0.12 + Source×0.08

## Architecture (Never Change Without Approval)
- `backend/main.py` = canonical entrypoint
- `webapp/routers/ingest.py` = Apify webhook handler
- `webapp/routers/rover.py` = recommendation engine
- `webapp/routers/outcomes.py` = deal outcomes tracking
- `backend/ingest/score.py` = DOS scoring engine
- `src/` = canonical frontend (React 18 + TypeScript + Tailwind)
- Rover is a FastAPI module — NOT a separate microservice
- No automated bidding ever
- No SaaS/multi-tenant features

## Security Rules (Flag Immediately)
- No hardcoded API keys, tokens, or secrets in any file
- All webhook endpoints must validate HMAC signature
- All user data endpoints must filter by authenticated user_id
- No service role client where anon client suffices
- Validate apify_run_id against regex before URL injection
- Zero-bid vehicles must never be scored (infinite ROI bug)

## Code Standards
- Python: FastAPI, Supabase client, proper error handling (fail closed, not open)
- JavaScript/TypeScript: No unguarded JSON.parse, no unguarded Date parsing
- All business rule constants defined at top of file, never inline magic numbers
- Every exception handler must log before returning generic error
- Never swallow DB write failures silently

## Known Issues Being Fixed (Don't Regress)
- Standard lane bid ceiling must be 0.80, NOT 0.88
- CURRENT_YEAR must be computed dynamically, not frozen at import time
- score.py: STANDARD_YEAR_CUTOFF must be CURRENT_YEAR - 4, not CURRENT_YEAR - 10
- score.py: Standard mileage max must be 50k, not 100k
- outcomes.py: get_outcomes_summary MUST filter by user_id
- rover.py: Recommendations must enforce business rules before returning
- ds-allsurplus: webhook secret must come from env var, not hardcoded

